<h1>Project Marky</h1>

A small <strong>Markdown</strong> demo for the <code>md_html.hmk</code> transpiler.

<h2>Features</h2>

<ul><li>Headings and <em>emphasis</em></li>
<li>Inline <code>code</code> spans</li>
<li><a href="https://example.com">Links</a> and lists</li>
</ul>
<h3>Ordered</h3>

<ol><li>first</li>
<li>second</li>
<li>third</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>A blockquote with a <strong>bold</strong> word. 
</blockquote>
<table><tr><td>Feature</td><td>Status</td></tr>
<tr><td>Tables</td><td>works</td></tr>
<tr><td>Code</td><td>masked</td></tr>
</table>
<hr/>

<pre><code class="language-python"># not a heading; **not** emphasis, a_b stays a_b
def hello(name):
    return f"hi {name}"  # [not](a-link)</code></pre>

Done with <code>**literal**</code> markdown left intact.
